TopicTitle: If I post my error.log can someone tell me which mod i'm crashing at loading?

Articles.Content:
Not sure what log file you posted but that one doesn't have the right info to see what mods you have but anyway it does tell that you hit the memory limit or are out of memory 

39% memory in use.
0 MB physical memory [0 MB free].
0 MB paging file [0 MB free].
0 MB user address space [130 MB free].

There's no official 64-bit KSP for Windows, so which tutorial did you follow to install the unofficial 64-bit hack? It looks like you're still running the 32-bit version of KSP and thus running out of memory.
Would help if you posted KSP.log, that'll show what it's loading and at what point it stops ( and usually why ).

There's no official 64-bit KSP for Windows, so which tutorial did you follow to install the unofficial 64-bit hack? It looks like you're still running the 32-bit version of KSP and thus running out of memory.

I am a huge idiot. I turned on 64 bit in the launcher because that option is still there, didn't even notice that it does nothing and it's still running in 32 bit and that's why i'm getting crashes. I found the community fix for 64 bit, installed it and I'm enjoying kerbal more than I ever have. Before I crashed every 15 minutes at least, plus had to turn things down to 1/8th textures, minimum detail, small resolution, open gl, and active texture management just to get my game to run. Now with the 64bit work-around i have max graphics settings, building huge ships, can play for hours with no issues whatsoever. It's finally enjoyable to play! loving it.

Thanks for the offer to help everyone. this was pure user error stupidity.
